FIX 2 — DEG & EG REPORT BUGS
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

Assessment values must be Yes or No only. Never Unknown.

Rules:
- Default = No.
- Yes only when annexure explicitly confirms DEG or EG presence with numeric evidence
  (Vendor CoA, DRL Specification, or USP <469> result).
- Never emit "Unknown" in Table 2, Section 5 Observations, or Section 6 Conclusion.

Filter Table 2:
- Stage section headers (Seal coating, Drug Loading, Sub Coating, Enteric coating,
  Lubrication, Inactive granules) must never appear as material rows.
- Aggregate duplicate materials using identity resolver (Hypromellose 5 cps ↔
  Hypromellose 5cps; Hydroxypropyl Cellulose ↔ Hydroxy Propyl Cellulose).
- Use real SAP material codes extracted from annexure CoAs (e.g. 100002851 for
  Polysorbate 80, 100003411 for Hypromellose, 100007331 for HPC Klucel EF).
- Never auto-generate M001-M999 fake codes. If no SAP code found, leave blank.

Conclusion narrative — no regulatory verification hedging:
Remove all mentions of:
- "manual review required"
- "assessment incomplete"
- "unresolved manual-review items"
- "cannot draw a final conclusion"
- "material-specific evidence not available"
- "supplier engagement needed"
- "USP <469> testing required"

Conclusion must be definitive:
- If all materials No/No: "Based on the overall assessment, there is no potential
  risk of Diethylene Glycol and Ethylene Glycol in [Product Name]. Hence, there is
  no requirement of drug product testing for DEG and EG."
- If positive with specification control: state specification limit and controlled
  through specification. State no drug product testing required.

Detail table structure (Table 3+) must exactly match approved format:
Columns (6 exactly):
  Excipients | Name | USP Monograph | Vendor COA | DRL Specification | DRL Specification No.

Rows (2 per positive material):
  Row 1: [material] | Diethylene Glycol (DEG) | NA | [vendor evidence or NA] | [DRL spec or NA] | [spec no]
  Row 2: [material] | Ethylene Glycol (EG)    | NA | [vendor evidence or NA] | [DRL spec or NA] | [spec no]

Footnote: "*Current version will be considered"

Values:
- USP Monograph: always "NA" (not extractable from CoA).
- Vendor COA: extracted numeric limit from annexure (e.g. "NMT 620 ppm") or "NA".
- DRL Specification: extracted numeric limit from annexure or "NA".
- DRL Specification No.: extracted spec no from annexure metadata (e.g. "SP-CFTO-003256-3")
  with "*" suffix, or blank.

Never render:
- "Refer applicable monograph" (use "NA").
- "Certificate of Analysis" in DRL Specification No. column (use actual spec no or blank).

Auto-fill:
- Header Strength field from composition strength columns (40 mg / 20 mg / 10 mg).
- Title default appends product name when title field only contains generic prefix.

Section 8 Change History must render in body (not just TOC).

